texts.text: Boss Update
For a guide about all the additions and changes in this update, see Bedrock Edition guides/Boss Update.

The Boss Update is the name for Minecraft: Pocket Edition version Alpha v0.16.0, an update that was released on October 21, 2016.[1] The iOS version was released a few days later on October 25, 2016.[2]
The official name for the update, the Boss Update, was revealed on August 29, 2016 in a blog post on the Mojang website.[3]
Contents

1 Notable features
1.1 Additions
1.2 Changes
2 Further revisions
3 Gallery
4 References
Notable features
Main articles: Pocket Edition v0.16.0 alpha and New Nintendo 3DS Edition 1.3.12
Additions

Lots of settings changes.
Add-ons.
Commands.
Ocean monuments.
4 new blocks:
Sea lantern, Prismarine, Wet sponge, and Beacons.
6 new items:
Prismarine crystals, Prismarine shards, the Nether star, and the Potion/Splash Potion/Arrow of Decay.
3 new mobs:
Guardian, Elder Guardian, and Wither.
Changes
Added sounds for various items, blocks, and mobs.
Further revisions

Alpha v0.16.1 fixed some bugs and crashes from Alpha v0.16.0.
Alpha v0.16.2 fixed some bugs from Alpha v0.16.1, and also added the Cartoon texture pack.
